    "analysis": "We previously ran a broad metric scan and obtained a top-20 list that included several DB nodes (db_001, db_003, db_005, db_006, db_007) with in-range P95 breaches. However, the targeted follow-up query limited to that DB candidate set returned zero rows (no in-range P95 breaches). This is a contradiction that must be resolved before we can localize the root cause. Per the diagnosis rules (confirm keys/fields when retrieval is empty), we should verify KPI availability and statistics for the DB candidates to ensure the KPI names and grouping used in the targeted query were correct and that we did not accidentally filter out relevant series. The next step is to list all KPI series for each of these DB nodes and compute global statistics (full-series P95 and counts) plus incident-window stats so we can see whether breaches exist, and if so which exact KPI names and timestamps correspond.\n",
